    "content": "<table style=\"margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" class=\"draggable toggleable-table\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th id=\"x\" style=\"text-align: right;\"><a href=\"/translate/\" target=\"_blank\">Contribute&nbsp;a&nbsp;translation</a></th>\n<th style=\"text-align: left;\">Source (English)</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\n<em>Shalom aleikhem, malaḥei hashalom</em>\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\nCalling oh angels, angles of peace.<br />\nMay peace bless our hearts<br />\nMay peace bless our homes<br />\nMay peace bless each one of us<br />\nSoul, flesh, and bone\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\nMay peace bless our waters<br />\nAnd the earth that grows our food,<br />\nMay peace bless the metals that connect us<br />\nand the hot fires that cook our food\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<hr />\n<p>These supplemental stanzas to the 1623 piyyut, &#8220;Shalom Aleikhem,&#8221; by Miriam Rubin, were offered on 9 January 2026.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n",
